ZH: 鬼火闪烁着微弱的光芒。
EN: The will-o'-the-wisp flickers with a faint glow.

ZH: 据传鬼火会引导人迷失于森林中。
EN: It is said that will-o'-the-wisps lead people astray in the forest.

ZH: 在黑暗中出现的鬼火往往令人恐惧。
EN: The appearance of will-o'-the-wisps in the dark often instills fear in people.

ZH: 他们告诉我，如果你追逐鬼火，你只会更迷失。
EN: They told me that if you chase will-o'-the-wisps, you will only get more lost.

ZH: 这个故事讲述了一个跟随鬼火的人的悲剧结局。
EN: This story tells the tragic ending of a person who followed a will-o'-the-wisp.

ZH: 那个夜晚，我在夜空中看到了一颗绿色的鬼火。
EN: That night, I saw a green will-o'-the-wisp in the night sky.

ZH: 鬼火随着风向移动，仿佛在引导我们前进。
EN: Will-o'-the-wisps move with the wind, as if guiding us forward.

ZH: 祖先们相信鬼火是来自亡灵的灵魂。
EN: Ancestors believed that will-o'-the-wisps were souls of the deceased.

ZH: 在某些地方，人们将鬼火视为不详的预兆。
EN: In some places, people see will-o'-the-wisps as ominous omens.

ZH: 鬼火聚集在沼泽地带，营造出诡异的景象。
EN: Will-o'-the-wisps gather in marshy areas, creating eerie scenes.

ZH: 我怀疑那个夜晚的鬼火是否真实存在。
EN: I doubt if the will-o'-the-wisp from that night truly existed.

ZH: 那名少年追逐着鬼火，最终走向了未知的命运。
EN: The young boy chased after the will-o'-the-wisp, ultimately heading towards an unknown fate.

ZH: 不要让鬼火的诱惑迷惑了你的前进方向。
EN: Don't let the temptation of the will-o'-the-wisp confuse your path forward.

ZH: 在故事中，鬼火能够帮助人们找到隐藏的宝藏。
EN: In the story, will-o'-the-wisps can help people find hidden treasures.

ZH: 几个朋友在森林中发现了一团闪烁的鬼火。
EN: A group of friends discovered a flickering will-o'-the-wisp in the forest.

ZH: 鬼火是黑暗中的微小亮点，但它们具有致命的吸引力。
EN: Will-o'-the-wisps are tiny points of light in the darkness, but they possess deadly allure.

ZH: 他们跟随鬼火的引导来到了一个神秘的废弃建筑物。
EN: They followed the guidance of the will-o'-the-wisp and arrived at a mysterious abandoned building.

ZH: 据说鬼火是亡灵对世界的联系。
EN: It is said that will-o'-the-wisps are the connection between the world of the living and the dead.

ZH: 鬼火的光芒越来越微弱，似乎在逐渐消失。
EN: The glow of the will-o'-the-wisp becomes increasingly faint as if gradually fading away.

ZH: 我的祖父告诉我鬼火在夜晚是最活跃的。
EN: My grandfather told me that will-o'-the-wisps are most active at night.
